The paper addresses the task of entity-relationship retrieval, which involves gathering and joining evidence from multiple unstructured documents. This task is closely related to information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP), which suggests that cs.IR and cs.CL are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for entity-relationship representations, which involves building on the basic early fusion design pattern for object retrieval. This suggests that cs.DB and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results using different query collections, which suggests that cs.LG is a possible sub-category as well.
